.TH RAZERCTL 1 "2026-06-21" "razerctl 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
razerctl \- control a Razer Blade 16 (fans, performance, keyboard, dGPU undervolt) on Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B razerctl
.RI [ command " [" args ]]
.PP
With no arguments,
.B razerctl
launches an interactive terminal dashboard (TUI).
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B razerctl
is the client for
.BR razerctld (8),
a background daemon that speaks Razer's USB-HID vendor protocol directly over
.IR hidraw
and owns the fan, performance mode, keyboard backlight, and battery charge
limit \(em persisting them to disk and re-applying them at boot. This client
is unprivileged: it sends commands to
.B razerctld
over a local socket and never needs root, except for the dGPU undervolt
subcommand/page (see below), which is unrelated to the daemon and talks to
NVIDIA's NvAPI directly.
.PP
It is unofficial and reverse-engineered, developed and tested on a 2024 Razer
Blade 16 (USB id \fB1532:02b7\fR). Opcodes can differ across models and firmware.
.SH THE DASHBOARD
Run
.B razerctl
with no arguments. Navigation is entirely by arrow keys:
.TP
.B Up / Down
move between settings
.TP
.B Left / Right
change the selected setting
.TP
.B Enter
open a sub-page or toggle the selected item
.TP
.B Esc
go back (from the dGPU undervolt page to the main page)
.TP
.B q
quit
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B get
Print the current performance mode, fan setpoint, and EPP.
.TP
.BI "mode " "balanced|gaming|creator"
Set the performance mode. On Linux the dGPU power ceiling is governed by NVIDIA
Dynamic Boost (\fInvidia-powerd\fR): Creator parks the GPU at its ~80\ W eco floor;
Balanced and Gaming allow boost.
.TP
.B fan auto
Hand the fans back to firmware control.
.TP
.BI "fan " RPM
Set a fixed fan RPM (2000\(en4800).
.TP
.B fancurve
Run a temperature-driven automatic fan curve (tracks CPU + dGPU temps).
.B Ctrl-C
restores auto.
.TP
.B rpm
Print live fan RPM on a 2-second loop.
.TP
.BI "battery " "50-100|off|status"
Set, disable, or read the EC battery charge limit. The stored percentage cannot
be read back (the firmware returns only a status byte), so confirm behaviorally \(em
charging should stop near the limit.
.TP
.BI "kbd " "white|red|purple|green|off"
Set the keyboard backlight to a solid colour preset, or turn it off.
.TP
.BI "epp " [0-255]
Show or set the CPU energy-vs-performance bias (intel_pstate HWP; 0 = max
performance, 255 = max power-save). Note: TLP resets EPP on every AC/battery
switch.
.TP
.BI "powerd " "on|off|status"
Toggle NVIDIA Dynamic Boost (\fInvidia-powerd\fR) at runtime. \fBoff\fR lets the
dGPU reach its near-0\ W deep-sleep state.
.TP
.BI "power " "max|save|status"
\fBmax\fR enables Dynamic Boost (up to ~175\ W); \fBsave\fR disables it; \fBstatus\fR
reports the current state.
.TP
.BI "uv " "mV min " [ max ]
Apply a dGPU undervolt: shift the voltage/frequency curve left by \fImV\fR for
clocks above \fImin\fR MHz, optionally capping the clock at \fImax\fR MHz. See
.B dGPU UNDERVOLT
below. Requires root.
.TP
.B uv reset
Reset the dGPU to its stock curve and clear the saved undervolt profile.
.TP
.B nvtest
Read-only diagnostic: dump the live VF curve and voltage. Works without root.
.SH DGPU UNDERVOLT
The dGPU undervolt shifts the GPU's voltage/frequency curve to run cooler and
quieter at the same clocks (like MSI Afterburner's curve undervolt). Settings:
.TP
.B Undervolt (mV)
How far to shift the curve left (lower voltage for a given clock). Start small,
e.g. 30\(en50 mV.
.TP
.B Min freq
Clocks below this stay at stock voltage (keeps idle stable).
.TP
.B Max freq
A hard clock ceiling, like a power slider.
.PP
Changing dGPU settings requires
.BR root .
Launch the tool with
.B sudo razerctl
to edit; a plain
.B razerctl
opens the dGPU page read-only (live readout visible, settings locked). The TUI
opens at Min freq 1695 MHz and Max freq 2400 MHz by default.
.PP
.B Warning:
if the panel is driven by the dGPU (BIOS dGPU-only / MUX mode), an unstable curve
can crash the display (recoverable). Tune gently \(em apply a modest offset,
confirm it holds under load, then push further.
.B Reset
returns to stock.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/razerctl-uv.conf
Saved undervolt profile, re-applied at login by the user service
.IR razerctl-uv.service .
The max-frequency cap is not auto-restored (it needs root).
.TP
.I /etc/udev/rules.d/99-razerctl.rules
udev uaccess rule granting your user access to the Razer HID device.
.SH NOTES
The fan tachometer reading ramps slowly (~40\(en50\ s to settle after a change).
The EC firmware has final say over fan speed and may override the requested value
as a thermal safeguard.
